# identification of genes for normalisation 

# As ERCC did not work for technical reasons, we needed to identify non-transcribed genes for normalisation.
# We noticed that, for Arabidopsis, non-transcribed genes tend to be down-regulated when comparing new and input samples under standard normalisation (see Supplemental Bioinformatic Methods).
# This is because their only source in the enriched fraction is non-specific carry-over.
